(side note: If it takes you 6hrs to do Zone_X with 30 ppl &lt;while skipping auxilarary content&gt;, and it takes us 3 hrs to do Zone_X with 60 ppl &lt;NOT skipping content&gt;, that's not Zerg.  Zerg (in my book) would be taking people above and beyond, without a corosponding drop in time taken to do content (e.g.  3 hrs to do Zone_X with 100 ppl))<br>
<br>
(side note #2:  If doing most with least is your thing, AND using more people than strictly nessesary equals zerging; then do you admit to &quot;zerging&quot; all those encounters that you bring 35 people to, but you've done in the past with 32?)<br>
<br>
-Tos has admitted that they are aware that the way they do the zone makes it far more likely that noone else will bother with the mobs they leave up, giving them almost exclusive raid content for the next day.  It sucks, but its allowed under SOES rules.<br>
<br>
And now back to your regularly schedualed random vitrol.<br>
